Rapper Jude Abaga aka M.I. has urged his colleagues to get their Permanent Voters Cards (PVCs) ahead of the 2023 general election. The record label executive and entrepreneur said this move will show the true leadership in everyone who carried out the exercise.   D’banj excites fans as Nigerian Idol audition show kicks off     Cremate my body when I die – Femi Kuti     Olamide hints at retiring after 12th album   M.I, in a short video shared on his social media pages, noted that getting the PVCs will send a powerful signal. He said: “I just have a thought that we need our celebrities, the people that spoke up for us, that protested with us.” - Advertisement - He continued saying: “I just want to ask my colleagues to get their PVC, you don’t need to do a campaign. Let’s get our PVCs ourselves, I know it’s not convenient but just go get your PVC if you don’t have it and show people that you’re ready. I think that’s a more powerful signal.”